The course starts with a description of professional practical training and how student can be successful in it.
In the course of this course, students will:
- Select a company for practical training base and apply for internship.
- Create a practical training plan in co-operation with a practical training base side supervisor.
- Complete the practical training.
- Create a practical training report and defend it.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the Practical Training is to acquire real work experience in an IT related company.
Practical Training will give students opportunities to acquire skills required for entering labor market and experience in:
- working in companies (key skills).
- the suitability of their personal characteristics (personal skills).
- the suitability and level of their acquired knowledge (skills related to education).
- potential opportunities for future career (career management skills).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On successful completion of this course, students should be able to work at IT company. Student has knowledges and experiences about - everyday working rutine; - quiddity of working at IT company; - sense of duty  and answer for job; - communication with company members and clients; - skills level and adeptness to study; - understanding studied courses items, relations and knowledges application to job tasks solutions.  Student has the big picture about his workplace position in practice base and also career opportunities in IT companies.
